","text":"For example, if a parent feature models a navigation stack of child features using the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackState","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" types, then it can perform its core logic "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" the logic","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of each child feature using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forEach"},{"text":" operator:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct ParentFeature {","  struct State {","    var path = StackState<Path.State>()","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case path(StackActionOf<Path>)","    \/\/ ...","  }","  var body: some ReducerOf<Self> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core parent logic","    }","    .forEach(\\.path, action: \\.path) {","      Path()","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"forEach","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" operator does a number of things to make integrating parent and child features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ergonomic and enforce correctness:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction\/element(id:action:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" action is sent it runs the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the parent feature to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction\/popFrom(id:)","isActive":true},{"text":" action is sent it runs the parent feature","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"before the child state is popped off the stack. This gives the parent feature an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"opportunity to inspect the child state one last time before the state is removed."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction\/push(id:state:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" action is sent it runs the parent feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"after the child state is appended to the stack. This gives the parent feature an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"opportunity to make extra mutations to the state after it has been added.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is removed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from the stack"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It gives the child feature access to the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"iden